# Trivy CVE waiver list — release.yml passes this file as --ignorefile.
#
# Trivy now scans for ALL fixed AND unfixed CRITICAL/HIGH CVEs (the
# previous --ignore-unfixed default silently shipped unfixed CRITICALs).
# Use this file to acknowledge specific CVEs that you've decided are
# acceptable for now, instead of disabling the whole "unfixed" category.
#
# RULES for adding an entry:
#   1. One CVE per line (just the CVE-YYYY-NNNNN id).
#   2. EVERY entry MUST carry a comment line above it with:
#         - owner (who's tracking this)
#         - reason (why it's safe / why no fix is available)
#         - review date (revisit if no fix lands by then)
#      An entry without that comment will be removed on the next audit.
#   3. Prefer fixing or upgrading the affected package over adding a waiver.
#
# Example:
#   # @mpofuslim — no fix from upstream for transitive netty path traversal
#   # in v4.2.x branch; not in the request-handling path on our use of
#   # spring-cloud-gateway. Review by 2026-09-01.
#   CVE-2026-12345
#
# (Empty — every CVE Trivy finds is currently either patched or otherwise
# absent from our build.)
